name: Shadows Of The Past
description:
The remains of last season's Lilac floret sprigs push against and support the fresh sprigs heavy with dew of the new season. The Lilac is a symbol of early growth, renewal, confidence, first love, magic and the transition from innocence to wisdom. (Syringa vulgaris)

2017. Nikon D60, 55-200mm Lens.

Photographed in situ, without the use of artificial lighting or staging. Photoshop only used for resizing.

1024x685 300dpi jpeg
